cs.AR, cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.SY, cs.LO

Reasoning: 
- cs.AR (Architecture): The paper focuses on modelling the timing aspects of binary programs running on architectures featuring caches and pipelines, which falls under the scope of this sub-category.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages): The paper deals with the worst-case execution time (WCET) of programs, which is a key concern in programming languages research.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper proposes a model-checking technique to compute tight bounds for WCET, which is a software engineering problem.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper deals with modelling and analyzing the behavior of systems (i.e., binary programs running on architectures featuring caches and pipelines) using timed automata, which is a topic of interest in this sub-category.
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science): The paper uses model-checking techniques, which are based on logical reasoning, to compute tight bounds for WCET, which is a topic of interest in this sub-category.
